<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1631" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1631">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/4.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the
                                    Navy</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: [After referring to the Navy Department’s
                            letters of December 11 and 13, and quoting the Minister’s telegram of
                            December 21, the letter continues:]</p>
                        <p>The Department would be glad to have you give it some expression as to an
                            arrangement that might be made by the Navy Department to handle all
                            wireless messages to and from the Republic of Panama.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>